<doc id="1118970" wikidata="Q111626" url="?curid=1118970" title="Rodengo-Saiano">
<text>Rodengo-Saiano (Brescian: ) is a &quot;comune&quot; in the province of Brescia, in Lombardy. A center of the Franciacorta historical region, it was founded in 1927 from the communes of Rodengo and Saiano.

It is home to a Cluniac monastery, the Abbazia di San Nicola (Abbey of St. Nicholas), founded in the mid-11th century.

==Twin towns==
* Kürten, Germany

