<doc id="1119170" wikidata="Q2095708" url="?curid=1119170" title="Shinchō">
<text>is a Japanese literary magazine published monthly by Shinchosha. Since its launch in 1904 it has published the works of many of Japan&#x27;s leading writers. Along with &quot;Bungakukai&quot;, &quot;Gunzo&quot;, &quot;Bungei&quot; and &quot;Subaru&quot;, it is one of the five leading literary journals in Japan.

The magazine features English translations of Japanese literary works. It presents the Shincho Literary Award.

==See also==
*List of literary magazines

