<doc id="1119229" wikidata="Q124121" url="?curid=1119229" title="Franciscus Irenicus">
<text>Franciscus Irenicus, byname of Franz Friedlieb (1494/1495 – 1553) was a German humanist, Protestant reformer and historian.

He was born in Ettlingen and died in Gemmingen. He studied at the famous Latin school in Pforzheim, where Philipp Melanchthon was a fellow student in 1508-09. As a patriotic humanist he describes Germany in twelve books: , which appeared in Hagenau in 1518.

==References==

Melanchthon, Philipp, &quot;Corpus Reformatorum&quot;, eds. K. Bretschneider and H. Bindseil, 28 vols (Halle: Schwetschke, 1834–60).

==External links==
